column1: #Text=Bayham is a municipality in Elgin County , Ontario .

#Text=Bayham is made up of several communities near Lake Erie , including Corinth , Eden , Froggetts Corners , North Hall , Port Burwell , Richmond , Springer 's Hill , Straffordville , Vienna and Wadger .
#Text=Bayham was named in 1810 for Viscount Bayham Charles Pratt , a friend of land grant recipient Colonel Talbot .
#Text=The nearest bus and train stations are 50 km away in Ingersoll .
#Text=By car , from Toronto , it 's about 200 km away : take Highway 401 west , then turn south on Culloden Line ( County Road 10 ) , and east on County Road 30 to Staffordville .
#Text=You can take County Road 19 south to Port Burwell .
#Text=The Museum of Naval History — HMCS Ojibwa , 3 Pitt Street , Port Burwell , ☏ +1 519-633-7641 , ✉ curator@elginmilitarymuseum.ca .
#Text=The HMCS Ojibwa is a Canadian Navy submarine brought to Port Burwell in 2013 .
#Text=Tours of the sub are offered daily .

#Text=Tourists can go on an external tour , where the guide will point out various features of the submarine 's external components , an interior tour , where a guide will take the tourists through all of the rooms on the submarine , or both .
#Text=Cameras are allowed outside of the submarine but not inside due to the sensitive nature of the equipment still on board .

#Text=Interior tour : adults $ 25 , children 6-13 $ 15 , children under 6 not permitted ; exterior tour adults $ 12.50 , children 6-13 $ 6 , children under 6 free ( taxes included ) ; both tours : adults $ 33 , children 6-13 $ 17 .

#Text=Port Burwell Provincial Park , 9 Wilson Lane , Port Burwell , ☏ +1 519-874-4691 .
#Text=The 2.5-km sandy beach is one of most beautiful on the northern shore of Lake Erie .
#Text=A family friendly campground with large , well-treed , level sites as well as an outstanding play area for kids .
#Text=Family-friendly Discovery Drop-ins from July 1st to Labour Day .
#Text=The park ’s three campgrounds are a short distance away from the lake in a mature forest and campsites are well-planned , easily accessible , large , private and many are grass-covered .
#Text=A recreation area features an amphitheater , children ’s playground , volleyball and badminton courts , horseshoe pits , ball diamond , Frisbee golf and a basketball foul shooting court .
